Gel lanes were cut into five bands
Comment[Instrument]: Ultimate 3000 nanoLC system (Dionex LC-Packings, Amsterdam, The Netherlands)
Q Exactive mass spectrometer (Thermo Fisher, Bremen, Germany)
Comment[IonizationType]: Eluting peptides were ionized at a potential of +2 kVa into a Q Exactive mass spectrometer (Thermo Fisher, Bremen, Germany).
Comment[GradientTime]: in a 10–40% buffer B gradient for 75 min (100 min inject-to-inject)
Comment[Separation]: peptides were separated using an Ultimate 3000 nanoLC system (Dionex LC-Packings, Amsterdam, The Netherlands)
Comment[FragmentMassTolerance]: fragment ions with a maximum mass deviation of 20 ppm
Comment[NumberOfMissedCleavages]: up to two missed cleavages were allowed.
